law.catch_line: Entry or survey of lands previously patented unlawful.
law.text: No person shall knowingly enter or have surveyed for patent, and no surveyor shall knowingly survey or certify for patent, any land that has previously, in whole or part, been entered or surveyed for patent, or patented.
law.history: Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 4705a.
